The paper deals with the problem of model uncertainty in autonomous systems, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of Bayesian methods and Markov decision processes suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on decision-making and optimization suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the use of probability theory and optimization techniques suggests that it could be categorized under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
